<title>USA: Horizon Bancorp Inc Q2 shr edges up.</title>
<headline>Horizon Bancorp Inc Q2 shr edges up.</headline>
<dateline>HUNTINGTON, W.Va. 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>For The Three  For The Six</p>
<p>					     Months Ended  Months Ended</p>
<p>						   June 30     June 30</p>
<p>					   1996    1995    1996    1995</p>
<p>Operating Results:</p>
<p> Interest income		  $12,371 $11,315 $24,550 $22,128</p>
<p> Interest expense		   4,852   4,389   9,743   8,275</p>
<p> Net interest income		7,519   6,926  14,807  13,853</p>
<p> Provision for loan losses	  314     268     649     485</p>
<p> Noninterest income		   822     663   1,609   1,266</p>
<p> Noninterest expense		4,655   4,304   9,201   8,553</p>
<p> Provision for income taxes     1,247     951   2,320   1,934</p>
<p> Net income			   2,125   2,066   4,246   4,147</p>
<p>Per Share of Common Stock:</p>
<p> Net income			    0.75    0.73    1.50    1.46</p>
<p> Dividends declared		  0.30    0.25    0.60    0.50</p>
<p>NOTE: 1996 six months results include non-recurring expenses related to the acquisition of Twentieth Bancorp Inc of about $800,000, of which about $250,000 was incurred in Q1 and about $550,000 in Q2.</p>
<p>---New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610</p>
